##Five prisons in three provinces have confirmed 555 cases, and the Ministry of Justice Talks about details of the outbreak

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Rinpei, thepaper.cn

On the morning of February 26, the State Council held a press conference on the joint prevention and control mechanism of COVID-19 infection and pneumonia to introduce the situation of the opinions of the political and legal organs on ensuring the resumption of work and production during the period of epidemic prevention and control according to law.

Given the recent surge in prison cases, how can the epidemic spread from prison to prison? What's the status of treatment? Vice Minister of Justice Xiong Xuanguo said that as of February 25, five prisons in three provinces had infected 555 cases, 19 suspected cases and 4 severe cases in Hubei, Zhejiang and Shandong. So far, there have been no deaths of prisoners infected with the new coronavirus. No other prisons in the country have reported any cases of criminal infection other than these five.

"The spread of the prison epidemic really reflects the loopholes in the prison management and the prevention and control of the epidemic. " Xiong said bluntly that the first is the lack of ideological attention, such as the Hubei Wuhan Women's prison, which is less than 100 meters from the Wuhan Lung Hospital, the commute of police officers to and from work and patients in lung hospitals are on the same bus stop, which may have led to the introduction of the virus before the full closure was achieved.".

The second is the lack of strict management. Xiong Xianguo said for example, the outbreaks in Hubei Hanjin prison, Zhejiang Shilifeng prison, and Shandong Rencheng District prison were all caused by the fact that individual police officers did not report truthfully that they had come into contact with people in the Hubei Epidemic area, and the isolation was not complete, which leads to an imported case.

"The spread of the epidemic in prisons has fully exposed the fact that these places do not have a deep understanding of ideology, the management of police officers is not strict, the implementation of prevention and control measures is not timely, and there are serious problems of formalism and bureaucracy in their work, " Xiong noted, the lessons learned from the prison epidemic are profound. The prison system throughout the country is fully aware of the particularity, complexity, severity and extreme importance of the prevention and control of the prison epidemic. It is strictly closed, strictly implemented, strictly responsible and strictly accountable, to eliminate loopholes in prison management and resolutely curb the spread of the prison epidemic, at the same time, we should make every effort to do rescue work. If a prisoner has fever or respiratory symptoms, he or she should be quarantined for observation at the first time. If a prisoner is diagnosed, he or she should be treated like any other member of society, equally timely treatment, 11 patients have been cured.
